{"questionId":"9118611","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><strong>Table 4</strong> shows the income tax rates in Kanyaland.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><strong>Table 4</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><strong><img src=\"__IMG__/7c1ecbc95af535124ecd0685dc7c5e9e14a23b18.png\"></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">Rufus and Sammy are citizens of Kanyaland. Rufus earns K$23 000 annually whereas Sammy earns K$46 000 annually.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Using <strong>Table 4</strong>,&nbsp;calculate the average tax rate for Sammy.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>22</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>×</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>20</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>000</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo> </mo><mo>+</mo><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>26</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>×</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>000</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo> </mo><mo>+</mo><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>30</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>×</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>8000</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo> </mo><mo>+</mo><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>34</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>×</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>8000</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo> </mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>12</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>120</mn></math></p>\n<p><em>Valid working (i.e. three of the four in parentheses correct) is sufficient for <strong>[1]</strong></em>.</p>\n<p><em>ATR </em>=<em>&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>12</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>120</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>46</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>000</mn></mrow></mfrac></math> </em>× 100 = 26.35 %</p>\n<p><strong><em>OR</em></strong></p>\n<p><em>ATR </em>=<em> <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>12</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>120</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>46</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>000</mn></mrow></mfrac></math> </em>= 0.26</p>\n<p><em>An answer of 26.35 or 0.26 w